WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:03.670
Greetings, TV audience.
I am ‐‐

00:03.670 --> 00:04.713
I‐I'll take it from here.

00:04.713 --> 00:05.589
Hi, there.

00:05.589 --> 00:07.299
I'm Dr. William DiMeo,

00:07.299 --> 00:09.968
San Diego's premier
cosmetic dentist.

00:09.968 --> 00:11.929
Dad, Uncle Billy's
commercial's on.

00:11.929 --> 00:13.680
Set chair to "brother."

00:13.680 --> 00:16.266
<i>I treat every smile</i>
<i>that walks through that door</i>

00:16.266 --> 00:17.434
<i>like it's my own.</i>

00:17.434 --> 00:18.227
<i>Scaler?</i>

00:18.227 --> 00:20.229
<i>Here, Doctor.</i>

00:20.229 --> 00:21.522
<i>I did her, too.</i>

00:21.522 --> 00:24.191
<i>And I want to give you</i>
<i>the DiMeo smile.</i>

00:24.191 --> 00:27.194
Do we have to spend Thanksgiving
with that narcissist?

00:27.194 --> 00:29.446
Well, we only see him
once a year.

00:29.446 --> 00:31.657
But shouldn't you see him
every six months?

00:31.657 --> 00:32.950
[ Chuckles ]
Dentist joke.

00:32.950 --> 00:34.493
<i>Whatever you need,</i>
<i>I'm your dentist.</i>

00:34.493 --> 00:35.494
[ Whistles ]

00:35.494 --> 00:37.496
‐Smile!
‐Smile, smile, smile!

00:37.496 --> 00:39.540
Hey, that's my line.

00:39.540 --> 00:40.415
Smile.

00:40.415 --> 00:41.166
[ Ding! ]

00:41.166 --> 00:42.292
Oh, make it stop.

00:43.669 --> 00:46.171
And... off.

00:47.089 --> 00:48.632
[ Sighs ]

00:48.632 --> 00:50.425
I don't care.

00:50.425 --> 00:51.718
It's worth it.

00:57.808 --> 01:00.102
I don't know if the sale rack
has anything

01:00.102 --> 01:01.979
for Thanksgiving
at the country club.

01:01.979 --> 01:04.189
Ooh, spoke too soon.

01:04.189 --> 01:07.192
Da‐da‐da‐da‐da.
Put that back.

01:07.192 --> 01:08.777
I'm the fancy bitch
in this family.

01:08.777 --> 01:10.320
Ray:
Why are we going at all?

01:10.320 --> 01:12.447
I hate Thanksgiving
with these guys.

01:12.447 --> 01:14.575
There's always so much
family drama.

01:14.575 --> 01:17.160
Remember when I said humidity
was my kryptonite?

01:17.160 --> 01:18.579
I was wrong.
It's drama.

01:18.579 --> 01:22.791
"So, in this,
you're Superman?"

01:22.791 --> 01:24.543
Ray's right.

01:24.543 --> 01:26.003
I mean, Billy and his perfect
family don't understand us,

01:26.003 --> 01:27.546
and they don't even try.

01:27.546 --> 01:30.257
We work bloody hard.
We deserve a fun Thanksgiving.

01:30.257 --> 01:32.384
Billy is my brother.
It's family.

01:32.384 --> 01:33.468
It matters.

01:33.468 --> 01:36.138
What in the world
is more important?

01:36.138 --> 01:37.681
[ <i>Choir vocalizes</i> ]

01:37.681 --> 01:41.143
Hey, thank you, TV,
for answering that question.

01:41.143 --> 01:43.645
We're gonna bail
and come buy this.

01:43.645 --> 01:44.604
‐Yes!
‐Yes!

01:44.604 --> 01:47.441
♪♪

01:47.441 --> 01:48.984
Kenneth!

01:48.984 --> 01:50.569
Jimmy and I
were just talking.

01:50.569 --> 01:52.863
We've decided to stay home
for Thanksgiving.

01:52.863 --> 01:54.531
As you're part
of the family now,

01:54.531 --> 01:56.116
we'd love for you
to join.

01:56.116 --> 01:58.452
And since it's tomorrow,
you get to act generous

01:58.452 --> 02:00.370
knowing I already have plans
and won't come.

02:00.370 --> 02:01.621
No.

02:01.621 --> 02:03.999
Great. I don't have plans.
I'd love to come.

02:03.999 --> 02:06.460
You don't have plans?!
What is wrong with you?

02:06.460 --> 02:07.919
Well, I didn't feel like
traveling this year,

02:07.919 --> 02:09.671
and some lady's making me
work on Friday.

02:09.671 --> 02:10.714
[ Laughs ]

02:10.714 --> 02:12.132
[ Sighs ] Fine.

02:12.132 --> 02:14.176
Bring your own plate.
We only have five.

02:14.176 --> 02:16.053
Right, darling,
everything's set.

02:16.053 --> 02:18.263
Black Friday plan,
friendless weirdo ‐‐

02:18.263 --> 02:20.349
time to call your brother
and cancel.

02:20.349 --> 02:22.267
You haven't told him
you're not coming yet?

02:22.267 --> 02:23.185
That's rude.

02:23.185 --> 02:24.978
Now, you see,
stuff like this ‐‐

02:24.978 --> 02:26.730
this is why you have
nowhere to go.

02:26.730 --> 02:30.776
Okay, team.
What is our excuse?

02:30.776 --> 02:32.986
I love a good family lie.
The house blew up?

02:32.986 --> 02:34.863
Last‐minute invitation
to Henry Winkler's.

02:34.863 --> 02:36.823
I have taken a lover.

02:36.823 --> 02:38.659
And JJ's sick it is.

02:38.659 --> 02:39.951
Ah, man.

02:39.951 --> 02:41.495
We use that excuse
for everything.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.413
I'm sorry,
you use your son's disability

02:43.413 --> 02:45.123
as your own personal
get‐out‐of‐jail‐free card?

02:45.123 --> 02:46.458
Don't judge us.

02:46.458 --> 02:47.876
Having an excuse
to get out of stuff

02:47.876 --> 02:50.629
is one of the, like,
three benefits of being
a special‐needs family.

02:50.629 --> 02:53.924
"There's skipping lines
at amusement parks."

02:53.924 --> 02:54.925
Good parking spots.

02:54.925 --> 02:56.301
And it's taught us lots

02:56.301 --> 02:58.178
about human dignity,
patience, and compassion.

02:58.178 --> 03:00.013
Blah, blah, blah.

03:00.013 --> 03:01.932
Hey, buddy.
It's Jimmy.

03:01.932 --> 03:04.851
We ‐‐ Yeah, we ‐‐ we saw
the new commercial.

03:04.851 --> 03:07.104
[ Laughing ] Funny.

03:07.104 --> 03:08.897
Yeah, we got that they
were all you.

03:08.897 --> 03:11.108
Listen, I hate to do this
at the last minute,

03:11.108 --> 03:12.526
but we got
to cancel tomorrow.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.318
Yeah, JJ's sick.

03:13.318 --> 03:14.403
[ Gags ]

03:14.403 --> 03:17.197
Yeah, on top of
the cerebral palsy.

03:17.197 --> 03:19.533
Yeah, that still
hasn't cleared up.

03:19.533 --> 03:22.244
Yeah, all right.
Okay, bye.

03:22.244 --> 03:25.080
Oh, well done, darling.

03:26.248 --> 03:27.833
‐They're coming here.
‐No!

03:27.833 --> 03:29.251
‐Crap!
‐No!

03:29.251 --> 03:32.587
We were so bloody close
to having a fun Thanksgiving.

03:32.587 --> 03:33.922
That's all I want.

03:33.922 --> 03:36.174
"Girls just want to have fun."
Lauper.

03:36.174 --> 03:38.468
Seriously.
I'm not being rude.

03:38.468 --> 03:40.929
Do you ever get invited
anywhere on purpose?

03:40.929 --> 03:42.222
Come on.

03:42.222 --> 03:44.099
What is so bad
about Jimmy's relatives?

03:44.099 --> 03:45.559
Oi! Everyone get in here.

03:47.018 --> 03:48.937
Kenneth wants to know

03:48.937 --> 03:51.273
what's so wrong
with Uncle Billy's family.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.023
Ugh.

03:52.023 --> 03:53.567
Let's start big picture.

03:53.567 --> 03:55.485
You'd think Jimmy's family,
after years with JJ,

03:55.485 --> 03:57.404
would have developed
some understanding,

03:57.404 --> 03:59.823
some extra care,
compassion.

03:59.823 --> 04:01.032
Instead what you get

04:01.032 --> 04:03.743
is a lot of talking
to JJ like he's deaf!

04:03.743 --> 04:07.247
Then there are these
individuals' specific quirks.

04:07.247 --> 04:08.248
Like cousin Duncan.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.833
Every year he has
a new catchphrase.

04:09.833 --> 04:11.918
Dope!

04:11.918 --> 04:14.004
Sick!

04:14.004 --> 04:15.755
[ Balls clack ]

04:15.755 --> 04:17.716
Noish!

04:17.716 --> 04:21.636
It will be the only thing
he says all day.

04:21.636 --> 04:28.185
"Aunt Audrey's mom puts on
a show for one lucky hostage."

04:28.185 --> 04:31.563
♪♪

04:31.563 --> 04:34.900
I'll assume that moving
is a standing ovation.

04:36.568 --> 04:39.237
Then there's Dr. Billy,
who is crazy‐rich

04:39.237 --> 04:41.865
and will not go a sentence
without reminding me.

04:41.865 --> 04:43.241
Billy: 3:15?

04:43.241 --> 04:43.992
Oh!

04:43.992 --> 04:47.204
Still on Saint‐Tropez time.

04:47.204 --> 04:49.623
Hey, you know
how to set a Rolex

04:49.623 --> 04:51.500
with diamonds
all around it?

04:51.500 --> 04:53.460
Then there's his wife,
Audrey.

04:53.460 --> 04:56.463
She apparently feels our pain
more than we do.

04:56.463 --> 05:01.051
Look at you all.
You're just so brave.

05:01.051 --> 05:02.636
[ Sobbing ]

05:02.636 --> 05:06.890
Oh, I'm sorry, JJ.
I'm leaving you out.

05:06.890 --> 05:09.351
[ Sobs ]

05:09.351 --> 05:11.102
You'll see.
Audrey's the worst.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.813
No one is worse
than Duncan.

05:12.813 --> 05:15.857
"Duncan doesn't give you
lap dances."

05:15.857 --> 05:20.570
I promise I'll be stuck watching
Audrey cry 10 times tomorrow.

05:20.570 --> 05:23.448
I bet you Billy humble‐brags
more than Audrey cries.

05:23.448 --> 05:24.741
‐I'll take that action.
‐I want in on this.

05:24.741 --> 05:26.576
"Deal me in, suckas!"

05:26.576 --> 05:27.577
Ooh, hold on!

05:27.577 --> 05:29.955
I know how to make
Thanksgiving fun.

05:29.955 --> 05:33.625
What if we turn
their annoyances into a game?

05:33.625 --> 05:36.002
Dylan gets a point every time
Duncan says his word.

05:36.002 --> 05:40.006
I get one when Audrey cries,
JJ when Joan dances,

05:40.006 --> 05:42.759
Jimmy when Billy humble‐brags,
and Ray ‐‐

05:42.759 --> 05:44.052
Wants no part of this.

05:44.052 --> 05:46.012
You're gonna try
and draw out

05:46.012 --> 05:48.265
more of the behavior
that drives you crazy.

05:48.265 --> 05:49.516
That's maximum drama.

05:49.516 --> 05:51.393
Good, 'cause we didn't
have anyone for you anyway.

05:51.393 --> 05:54.312
I'm actually looking forward
to Thanksgiving.

05:54.312 --> 05:56.773
Not since
"A Spoonful of Sugar"

05:56.773 --> 05:59.568
has a British lady made
something so crappy fun.

05:59.568 --> 06:00.610
Mwah.

06:00.610 --> 06:03.363
"Does the game
have stakes?"

06:03.363 --> 06:07.576
You know how every year
Uncle Billy always slips Dad

06:07.576 --> 06:09.202
a wad of pity cash?

06:09.202 --> 06:10.912
Winner takes all.

06:10.912 --> 06:13.415
Now that's something
to be thankful for.

06:13.415 --> 06:15.083
Noish!

06:15.083 --> 06:17.419
Happy Thanksgiving, Ray.

06:17.419 --> 06:19.004
Why did you
come here?

06:19.004 --> 06:20.881
It's your day off.
Run.

06:20.881 --> 06:22.340
You keep stressing
like that,

06:22.340 --> 06:23.842
you're gonna give yourself
an ulcer.

06:23.842 --> 06:26.469
At least then my acid reflux
would have a friend.

06:26.469 --> 06:28.263
Listen,
I hate drama, too.

06:28.263 --> 06:30.724
Last year, I was the victim
of identity theft.

06:30.724 --> 06:32.475
Just let the guy
keep my name.

06:32.475 --> 06:33.768
You need to fix that.

06:33.768 --> 06:35.478
Eh. Actually improved
my credit.

06:36.730 --> 06:39.399
Look, if you really
want to avoid drama

06:39.399 --> 06:42.485
at a family event,
there's only one play.

06:42.485 --> 06:44.154
Hide out in the kitchen.

06:44.154 --> 06:45.864
But my mom's in there.

06:45.864 --> 06:48.033
It's the epicenter
of drama.

06:48.033 --> 06:51.536
Which is why you and I will be
taking over the cooking.

06:51.536 --> 06:53.038
Oh. Likey.

06:53.038 --> 06:54.623
Don't do that.

06:54.623 --> 06:56.207
[ Doorbell rings ]

06:56.207 --> 06:57.459
They're here!

06:57.459 --> 07:00.420
Okay, contestants,
on your marks, get set...

07:00.420 --> 07:01.421
go.

07:01.421 --> 07:03.632
‐Hello, everyone.
‐There she is!

07:03.632 --> 07:04.966
Hi. Thank you.

07:04.966 --> 07:06.718
So good to see you.

07:06.718 --> 07:08.845
Oh, hey, Jimbo.

07:08.845 --> 07:10.639
Are you doing
a house‐flip thing here?

07:10.639 --> 07:11.640
Smart.

07:11.640 --> 07:13.600
Huh? This is quite
the "before" pic.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.060
[ Chuckles ] Judges?

07:15.060 --> 07:16.770
Douchey, not a brag.

07:16.770 --> 07:18.021
Oh, hey, hey, hey.

07:18.021 --> 07:20.023
Who wants to see
my newest satisfied customer?

07:20.023 --> 07:21.650
[ Snaps ]
Open up. Huh?

07:21.650 --> 07:23.318
Ah!

07:23.318 --> 07:24.444
‐Wow.
‐He'll grow into those.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.154
‐Hey, Duncan.
‐Hm.

07:27.614 --> 07:28.490
Denied.

07:28.490 --> 07:31.409
There he is.

07:31.409 --> 07:34.746
I have something
"muy caliente" prepared.

07:34.746 --> 07:36.665
My biggest fan...

07:36.665 --> 07:39.042
meet my newest fan.

07:39.042 --> 07:40.251
[ Chuckles ]

07:40.251 --> 07:42.253
You want me
to dance already?

07:42.253 --> 07:43.672
No, "pathienthia."

07:43.672 --> 07:45.965
Oh, good,
he's feeling better.

07:45.965 --> 07:49.427
Hi, JJ!
Gobble, gobble!

07:49.427 --> 07:51.262
His hearing
is actually perfect.

07:51.262 --> 07:53.223
He just can't speak.

07:53.223 --> 07:54.766
Oh, well,
not yet he can't.

07:54.766 --> 07:57.185
[ Voice breaking ] But you
never give up hope, do you?

07:57.185 --> 08:00.480
[ Crying ]
Oh, I'm sorry, I ‐‐

08:00.480 --> 08:03.942
Aw. Yes.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.110
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]
‐Suck it.

08:08.613 --> 08:09.698
There we go.

08:09.698 --> 08:11.324
Your mom gave us
the kitchen,

08:11.324 --> 08:13.034
and I've created
a drama force field.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.202
[ Chuckles ]

08:14.202 --> 08:15.829
Now, let's get down
to business.

08:15.829 --> 08:17.163
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:17.163 --> 08:19.249
How do you cook?

08:19.249 --> 08:21.251
You've never
done this before?

08:21.251 --> 08:22.836
How hard could it be?

08:22.836 --> 08:24.629
We just got to get this turkey
out of here.

08:24.629 --> 08:27.006
It's taking up all the space
in the one oven that works.

08:27.006 --> 08:29.634
Mom said two more hours
at 325.

08:29.634 --> 08:32.929
Sounds like one more hour
at 650 to me.

08:32.929 --> 08:35.724
Or 39,000 degrees
for one minute.

08:35.724 --> 08:37.892
Did you just do that
in your head?

08:37.892 --> 08:39.686
Damn, you're a good chef!

08:39.686 --> 08:42.355
♪♪

08:42.355 --> 08:44.315
And here's
the bathroom.

08:44.315 --> 08:46.651
Just one to service
the whole family.

08:46.651 --> 08:47.819
Very sad.

08:47.819 --> 08:51.072
Note the lack of door.

08:51.072 --> 08:53.700
Maybe Santa
will bring us one.

08:53.700 --> 08:56.077
And yet,
still you rise.

08:56.077 --> 08:58.121
[ Crying ]
I don't know how you do it.

08:58.121 --> 08:59.706
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]
‐Sorry.

08:59.706 --> 09:02.375
When I'm pregnant,
I get so much more emotional.

09:02.375 --> 09:04.044
Oh, I didn't even
think of that.

09:07.047 --> 09:08.840
Check out
these video games.

09:08.840 --> 09:10.341
Pretty sick, huh?

09:10.341 --> 09:13.136
Or whatever word really cool
people are using.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.139
Come on, dude,
what's it gonna take?

09:16.139 --> 09:18.683
I've got comic books.

09:18.683 --> 09:20.560
Bag of Ray's
baby teeth.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.687
Lite‐Brite?

09:22.687 --> 09:24.189
Yaaass!

09:24.189 --> 09:25.690
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]
‐Yes!

09:27.484 --> 09:28.610
Yaaass!

09:28.610 --> 09:29.819
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]

09:33.656 --> 09:35.283
[ Flamenco music playing ]

09:35.283 --> 09:36.910
[ Castanets clacking ]

09:36.910 --> 09:39.704
JJ is loving this
more than usual.

09:39.704 --> 09:41.372
It must be the dress.

09:41.372 --> 09:42.540
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]

09:42.540 --> 09:44.167
You're wasting time,
darling.

09:44.167 --> 09:46.044
Everyone else
is racking up the points.

09:46.044 --> 09:48.463
Oh, yeah,
hope I can catch up.

09:48.463 --> 09:49.589
Yeah.

09:49.589 --> 09:51.883
Thanks, bro.

09:51.883 --> 09:53.093
[ Clears throat ]

09:53.093 --> 09:54.177
So...

09:54.177 --> 09:55.804
You saw the new Tesla,
right?

09:55.804 --> 09:57.597
Everyone wants
to look inside it.

09:57.597 --> 10:00.475
Like they've never seen a rich
guy save the planet before.

10:00.475 --> 10:01.559
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]

10:01.559 --> 10:03.520
Took it to Vegas,
lost 15 grand...

10:03.520 --> 10:06.189
in taxes that I paid
on my winnings.

10:06.189 --> 10:07.107
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]

10:07.107 --> 10:08.650
Oh, God,
my last commercial,

10:08.650 --> 10:10.944
it was so huge,
it's like, how do I top it?

10:10.944 --> 10:12.028
You know?

10:12.028 --> 10:13.655
I was gonna shoot it
on my yacht,

10:13.655 --> 10:16.032
but apparently,
"You need permits, sir."

10:16.032 --> 10:17.534
[ Chuckles ]
I don't know.

10:17.534 --> 10:20.411
I should just run for mayor.
Everyone's asking me to.

10:20.411 --> 10:22.205
I'll finally get 'em
off my ass, you know?

10:22.205 --> 10:23.039
[ Laughs ]

10:23.039 --> 10:24.541
[ <i>Ding ding ding!</i> ]

10:24.541 --> 10:25.875
So, things are good.

10:29.546 --> 10:32.799
Okay, outside is burnt,

10:32.799 --> 10:34.717
but inside is, uh...

10:34.717 --> 10:36.636
75 degrees!

10:36.636 --> 10:40.640
Okay, so what we need to do
is take some of this cook

10:40.640 --> 10:42.308
and put it in here.

10:42.308 --> 10:44.936
So much for avoiding drama.
We've ruined Thanksgiving.

10:44.936 --> 10:46.354
Ruined?

10:46.354 --> 10:47.856
Hey, have you ever been
to the supermarket?

10:47.856 --> 10:50.275
They have a whole case
full of cooked baby turkeys.

10:50.275 --> 10:52.235
Those are
rotisserie chickens.

10:52.235 --> 10:54.863
Well, you know that
because you are a chef.

10:54.863 --> 10:58.783
No, I'm sorry, darling.
That only counts as one dance.

10:58.783 --> 11:01.452
"She changed ‐‐" S‐T‐Y‐‐
"styles five times."

11:01.452 --> 11:02.620
It's a medley, JJ.

11:02.620 --> 11:04.789
What can I say?
My hands are tied.

11:04.789 --> 11:08.126
[ Sighs ] Mark me down
for two more yaaasses.

11:08.126 --> 11:08.918
He is on fire.

11:08.918 --> 11:10.378
That's good, darling,

11:10.378 --> 11:12.547
but we're all playing
for second place.

11:12.547 --> 11:15.049
Your dad's cleaning up,
and he's not even trying.

11:15.049 --> 11:17.594
I'm done playing the market.
Who needs the stress?

11:17.594 --> 11:18.720
One day I lose 10K,

11:18.720 --> 11:20.388
‐then I make 100K...
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]

11:20.388 --> 11:22.432
...then I lose 5K,
then I make 200K.

11:22.432 --> 11:24.225
[ <i>Ding!</i> ]
‐Get me off this ride!

11:24.225 --> 11:25.643
You and me both, buddy.

11:25.643 --> 11:27.270
♪♪

11:27.270 --> 11:29.355
See? I told you
this plan was perfect.

11:29.355 --> 11:32.192
You think they'll notice that
our turkey has 16 tiny legs?

11:32.192 --> 11:35.111
Nah, with the amount of hormones
they pump into these birds,

11:35.111 --> 11:37.614
there's no right number of legs
a turkey has anymore.

11:37.614 --> 11:39.741
Okay, drama averted.

11:39.741 --> 11:42.619
[ Cellphone rings ]

11:42.619 --> 11:44.287
Excuse me.

11:45.830 --> 11:47.999
[ Cellphone beeps ]

11:47.999 --> 11:49.542
Take a hint!

11:49.542 --> 11:51.336
When it rings once
and it goes to voicemail,

11:51.336 --> 11:52.670
I'm ignoring you!

11:52.670 --> 11:54.214
Stop calling me, woman!

11:54.214 --> 11:55.173
[ Cellphone beeps ]

12:00.053 --> 12:02.388
We're gonna need some bowls
for this stuff.

12:04.724 --> 12:07.602
You know, Ray, uh, I wonder
if you noticed back there,

12:07.602 --> 12:08.436
I took a call.

12:08.436 --> 12:09.771
I caught that, yeah.

12:09.771 --> 12:11.689
It's just a little
family stuff.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.691
It's why I chose
to be here today.

12:13.691 --> 12:16.444
And now I feel like I ruined
our peaceful vibe.

12:16.444 --> 12:19.239
No, nothing's ruined.
We still got a nice mellow ‐‐

12:19.239 --> 12:21.950
It's just that my sister Kendall
comes into town,

12:21.950 --> 12:23.326
and she gets with my mom,

12:23.326 --> 12:25.495
and it's just
Crap on Kenneth Day.

12:25.495 --> 12:26.996
So, back to the food ‐‐

12:26.996 --> 12:28.331
And then my dad joins in,

12:28.331 --> 12:31.334
and God forbid say anything
against the colonel.

12:31.334 --> 12:33.461
This is starting
to feel like drama.

12:33.461 --> 12:36.798
You're gonna attack me
now, too, NC?

12:36.798 --> 12:39.008
That's for "New Colonel."

12:39.008 --> 12:40.593
I don't want to be
the new colonel.

12:40.593 --> 12:43.054
And I don't want to be the
Clements family disappointment.

12:43.054 --> 12:46.140
Okay, four seconds ago,
I didn't know your last name.

12:46.140 --> 12:47.642
Let's go back to that.

12:47.642 --> 12:49.060
So what are you driving
these days?

12:49.060 --> 12:51.854
Same wheelchair‐accessible van
we've had for a decade.

12:51.854 --> 12:53.731
Good for you,
because honestly ‐‐

12:53.731 --> 12:54.732
Oh, let me guess.

12:54.732 --> 12:56.401
I'm lucky
I drive a crappy car.

12:56.401 --> 12:58.194
Owning great things
is the worst.

12:58.194 --> 12:59.153
Being rich sucks?

12:59.153 --> 13:00.905
Easy.

13:00.905 --> 13:03.408
I'm just saying it's stressful
having all that horsepower.

13:03.408 --> 13:04.284
Oh, shut up.

13:04.284 --> 13:05.410
What is this constant need

13:05.410 --> 13:06.911
to prove that you're better
than me?

13:06.911 --> 13:07.912
We're not 13.

13:07.912 --> 13:09.455
I'm a 13 handicap.

13:09.455 --> 13:12.125
Ugh, enough about
the golf and the yacht.

13:12.125 --> 13:14.419
You forgot the car,
which I'm very, very proud of.

13:14.419 --> 13:15.628
Well, guess what.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.922
I could outrace you
in your Tesla

13:17.922 --> 13:20.258
with my old junker any day.

13:20.258 --> 13:21.676
Oh, it's on.

13:21.676 --> 13:22.468
It's on.

13:22.468 --> 13:23.136
No.

13:24.429 --> 13:26.264
Now it's on.

13:26.264 --> 13:28.182
‐The car?
‐Turned it on with my phone.

13:28.182 --> 13:30.310
Well, that actually
is pretty cool.
Yep.

13:30.310 --> 13:32.478
See what you do to me, Ray?

13:32.478 --> 13:35.732
You find my insecurities,
and you poke.

13:35.732 --> 13:37.775
And you poke,
and you poke!

13:37.775 --> 13:39.068
I don't think I poked,

13:39.068 --> 13:41.320
but if there was
any unintentional poking ‐‐

13:41.320 --> 13:42.780
[ Laughing ]
Oh, yeah. Yeah.

13:42.780 --> 13:44.282
You'd fit just fine
in my family.

13:44.282 --> 13:45.658
[ Chuckles ]

13:45.658 --> 13:46.868
Just fine.

13:46.868 --> 13:49.078
Look, the holidays
are a tricky time.

13:49.078 --> 13:51.372
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Play it cool.

13:51.372 --> 13:53.499
Make me out to be
the crazy one.

13:53.499 --> 13:55.543
Crazy Kenneth!

13:55.543 --> 13:57.462
Oh, hell no!

13:57.462 --> 14:00.590
You did not just walk away
from me.

14:00.590 --> 14:02.675
Mom!

14:02.675 --> 14:04.427
[ Engine revving ]

14:08.389 --> 14:10.099
What is going on here?

14:10.099 --> 14:11.851
What does it look like,
dear?

14:11.851 --> 14:13.644
It's a driving‐skills
competition.

14:13.644 --> 14:16.022
Is that my granny's urn?

14:17.023 --> 14:19.859
[ Imitates engine revving ]

14:19.859 --> 14:21.152
It's electric car.
It doesn't rev.

14:21.152 --> 14:22.236
[ Imitates engine revving ]

14:22.236 --> 14:23.946
Honey,
is this a good idea?

14:23.946 --> 14:25.782
Honey, stay out of it.

14:25.782 --> 14:27.075
I've stayed out of it.

14:27.075 --> 14:28.785
That's what got us
into this mess.

14:28.785 --> 14:29.827
I'm doing it.

14:29.827 --> 14:31.079
Jimmy, you ready?

14:32.455 --> 14:34.207
‐Three, two...
‐No!

14:34.207 --> 14:36.751
Don't wreck the car!
It's a rental.

14:36.751 --> 14:38.503
[ Sighs ]

14:38.503 --> 14:40.505
It's true.
We're broke.

14:40.505 --> 14:42.131
We've lost everything.

14:42.131 --> 14:43.466
‐What?
‐Really?

14:48.638 --> 14:50.264
I gambled it all away.

14:50.264 --> 14:52.433
And then I tried to claw
my way back

14:52.433 --> 14:54.352
by selling
unnecessary procedures ‐‐

14:54.352 --> 14:58.064
braces for babies,
everybody got a night guard.

14:58.064 --> 15:01.359
And then Channel 10 blew the lid
off the whole damn thing.

15:01.359 --> 15:04.487
But, hey, hey, hey.
We're gonna get it all back.

15:04.487 --> 15:07.406
Look what I built
with just a dental degree

15:07.406 --> 15:09.534
and 800 grand
from your dad.

15:09.534 --> 15:10.952
What's going on?

15:10.952 --> 15:14.330
We were having a really nice day
until it all got ruined

15:14.330 --> 15:16.541
because of this
stupid competition.

15:16.541 --> 15:18.918
What did I tell you?
So, they bug you.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.211
Deal with it.

15:20.211 --> 15:21.546
Instead you turned them
into pawns

15:21.546 --> 15:24.549
in your stupid
mocking game.

15:24.549 --> 15:25.424
Game?

15:25.424 --> 15:27.218
What game?

15:27.218 --> 15:28.845
They didn't know
about that part, son.

15:28.845 --> 15:30.638
Drama, drama, drama.

15:30.638 --> 15:33.850
Damn you
and your drama, NC!

15:33.850 --> 15:36.269
I don't want to be
the new colonel.

15:39.564 --> 15:41.524
So, that's all we are to you?
The butt of some cruel joke?

15:41.524 --> 15:42.608
Audrey:
What were you betting on?

15:42.608 --> 15:44.152
[ Voice breaking ]
I mean, what do I do

15:44.152 --> 15:45.611
that's so ridiculous
anyway?

15:45.611 --> 15:47.113
Nothing, we ‐‐
we didn't have one for you.

15:47.113 --> 15:48.781
Okay.

15:48.781 --> 15:51.075
You want to play a game
about people's annoying stuff?

15:51.075 --> 15:54.412
Because we can play a game
about people's annoying stuff.

15:54.412 --> 15:56.998
Like, I don't know,
a sister‐in‐law that goes on

15:56.998 --> 15:58.666
like a British
Erin Brockovich.

15:58.666 --> 16:01.752
[ Cockney accent ] I took on
the system, I did, I did.

16:01.752 --> 16:03.880
Yeah, tell her, honey.
Meh, meh.

16:03.880 --> 16:05.965
Witty wisecrack.
Meh, meh, meh.

16:05.965 --> 16:08.176
That's pretty good.
Maya: No, no, it's good,
it's good, it's good.

16:08.176 --> 16:09.802
Get it out, get it out,
whether it's accurate or not.

16:09.802 --> 16:11.429
Oh, and don't forget
about JJ.

16:11.429 --> 16:13.139
He's got that sick
"Harold and Maude" thing

16:13.139 --> 16:14.056
going on with Joan.

16:14.056 --> 16:18.060
"I do.
Sorry, society."

16:18.060 --> 16:20.646
But you guys can mock us
all you want

16:20.646 --> 16:22.899
because you've
got problems.

16:22.899 --> 16:24.192
No, no, no, you're right.

16:24.192 --> 16:26.235
We ‐‐ We're so focused
on the fact that you

16:26.235 --> 16:27.612
don't understand
our problems.

16:27.612 --> 16:30.114
We didn't even consider
that you might actually

16:30.114 --> 16:31.866
have problems
of your own.

16:31.866 --> 16:33.159
This is good, you know,

16:33.159 --> 16:35.411
'cause we're actually talking
about something.

16:35.411 --> 16:36.996
Yeah, like a family.

16:36.996 --> 16:39.123
You annoy us,
we annoy you.

16:39.123 --> 16:40.791
I'm glad the game
came out.

16:40.791 --> 16:42.501
What game?

16:42.501 --> 16:45.838
And you see, Ray, that is how
you enter a conversation.

16:45.838 --> 16:48.341
It really seemed like you
were talking about the game.

16:48.341 --> 16:50.468
Maybe this can be
a fresh start.

16:50.468 --> 16:53.095
Maybe our Thanksgiving
can be something different.

16:53.095 --> 16:56.015
And maybe we don't even have
any turkey or sides.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.683
I love that idea, Maya.

16:57.683 --> 17:00.811
Billy...

17:00.811 --> 17:02.396
let's take a walk.

17:05.983 --> 17:07.151
[ Door opens ]

17:07.151 --> 17:08.861
Ray. Hey, man.

17:08.861 --> 17:10.279
In the harsh
light of day,

17:10.279 --> 17:13.282
I may been working
through some stuff

17:13.282 --> 17:16.494
and unfairly transferred
some things onto you.

17:16.494 --> 17:17.203
It's okay.

17:17.203 --> 17:18.829
Could you have handled it

17:18.829 --> 17:20.998
a little bit better
than you did?

17:20.998 --> 17:24.001
Doesn't matter.
Happy Thanksgiving.

17:24.001 --> 17:26.420
This is nice,
just you and me.

17:26.420 --> 17:27.546
We never do this.

17:27.546 --> 17:28.631
No.

17:28.631 --> 17:30.591
Kid wasn't sick, was he?

17:30.591 --> 17:31.842
You just didn't
want to come.

17:31.842 --> 17:33.261
Ah.

17:33.261 --> 17:35.596
How much honesty
were you looking for today?

17:35.596 --> 17:36.806
[ Sighs ]

17:36.806 --> 17:40.184
Look, I get that you guys
have stuff going on,

17:40.184 --> 17:44.397
but people have problems
and brothers at the same time.

17:44.397 --> 17:46.774
That's the first thing
you've said in 10 years

17:46.774 --> 17:49.235
that isn't about how much
stuff you've got.

17:49.235 --> 17:52.321
Yeah, well, I'm poor now.
I got to mix it up.

17:52.321 --> 17:54.657
For the record,
we didn't just cancel

17:54.657 --> 17:57.118
because we didn't
want to hang out with you.

17:57.118 --> 17:59.453
Oh, no?
What, you got big plans?

17:59.453 --> 18:01.998
Huge.

18:01.998 --> 18:03.541
60 inches.

18:03.541 --> 18:06.586
♪♪

18:06.586 --> 18:08.254
Audrey: Wow, long line.

18:08.254 --> 18:10.756
I'm not sure
you're gonna get your TV.

18:10.756 --> 18:11.924
Ooh, where you going?

18:12.800 --> 18:14.969
"I know a guy."

18:21.434 --> 18:22.310
Is this okay?

18:22.310 --> 18:23.519
Yeah, just go with it.

18:23.519 --> 18:25.104
Thank you.

18:25.104 --> 18:26.814
Oh, whoa, whoa.
What the hell?

18:26.814 --> 18:28.566
I've been sitting here
for 36 hours.

18:28.566 --> 18:33.362
"I've been sitting here
for 16 years."

18:39.035 --> 18:41.162
Yaaass!

18:41.162 --> 18:44.749
What is yaaass?

18:44.749 --> 18:46.792
I guess it's my way
of compensating for the fact

18:46.792 --> 18:48.711
that sometimes
I feel I have nothing of value

18:48.711 --> 18:50.046
to contribute
to a conversation.

18:50.046 --> 18:51.589
It's ‐‐ It's like
verbal armor.

18:51.589 --> 18:53.883
No, I just meant,
what is it?

18:53.883 --> 18:55.009
Oh, it's like "yes."

18:57.053 --> 19:00.765
[ Crying ] I just ‐‐
I don't have any words.

19:00.765 --> 19:04.143
It's just so good.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.561
Oh, God.

19:05.561 --> 19:09.315
So, I shouldn't be insulted
that you cried about me at all.

19:09.315 --> 19:10.650
You're just nuts.

19:10.650 --> 19:12.818
So nuts.

19:12.818 --> 19:14.945
[ Sobbing ]

19:14.945 --> 19:17.657
Damn it, Kendall!
Let your brother get a word in!

19:19.075 --> 19:23.120
I'm calling because...

19:23.120 --> 19:25.081
I was inspired
to make things right.

19:26.290 --> 19:28.417
No, no, don't put
the colonel on.

19:28.417 --> 19:29.335
I'll ‐‐

19:29.335 --> 19:31.545
I ain't gonna
talk to him 'cause...

19:31.545 --> 19:32.463
Hello, sir!

19:32.463 --> 19:34.840
Okay, let's load
this sucker up.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.676
[ Crowd groans ]
‐Wow.

19:36.676 --> 19:39.512
Actually,
change of plans.

19:39.512 --> 19:40.888
Excuse me.

19:40.888 --> 19:42.473
Hi.

19:42.473 --> 19:46.227
I just bought the last
60‐inch super‐high‐def TV.

19:46.227 --> 19:48.145
It lists at $1,000.

19:48.145 --> 19:51.023
The bidding
starts at $200.

19:51.023 --> 19:52.024
Are you kidding me?

19:52.024 --> 19:53.401
‐$200!
‐$250!

19:56.696 --> 19:58.239
Enjoy.

20:01.659 --> 20:02.493
No. What?

20:02.493 --> 20:03.953
I can't.
No way.

20:03.953 --> 20:05.788
Please.

20:05.788 --> 20:07.581
How many times have you helped
my family out over the years?

20:07.581 --> 20:08.374
13.

20:08.374 --> 20:09.291
Okay.

20:09.291 --> 20:11.252
Well, that wasn't
just for you.

20:11.252 --> 20:13.546
I really like stuff
being all about me.

20:13.546 --> 20:15.172
Sure.

20:15.172 --> 20:17.967
Here.
Here you go.

20:17.967 --> 20:19.677
Buy yourself
something nice, kid.

20:19.677 --> 20:20.511
Okay.

20:22.763 --> 20:24.348
Well, that was lovely.

20:24.348 --> 20:25.516
Hm.

20:25.516 --> 20:27.393
We really do host
a very nice Thanksgiving.

20:27.393 --> 20:28.519
Yeah.

20:28.519 --> 20:30.521
Except we didn't
feed them.

20:30.521 --> 20:33.315
Let's go home
and have some turkey.

20:33.315 --> 20:35.526
Sorry, no can do.
JJ's sick.

20:41.657 --> 20:43.200
<i>Hi, I'm Dr. William DiMeo.</i>
<i>Just one of me this time.</i>

20:43.200 --> 20:46.787
<i>In dentistry, like in life,</i>
<i>there are ups and downs.</i>

20:46.787 --> 20:50.374
<i>But you know what's constant?</i>
<i>Family.</i>

20:50.374 --> 20:53.294
<i>Like JJ, my real‐life nephew.</i>

20:53.294 --> 20:55.671
<i>If he likes me,</i>
<i>I can't be all bad, huh?</i>

20:55.671 --> 20:58.591
Are we okay with him using JJ
to get his patients back?

20:58.591 --> 20:59.967
Shh!

20:59.967 --> 21:03.012
So take it from loveable,
trustworthy JJ,

21:03.012 --> 21:06.640
and come on back and let me
give you the DiMeo smile.

21:06.640 --> 21:07.850
Special holiday offer ‐‐

21:07.850 --> 21:09.727
two teeth whitenings
for the price of one.

21:09.727 --> 21:10.728
[ Ding ding! ]
